.\" termin.al-name: man
.\" termin.al-usage: man [-P less|vi] [--pager=less|vi] <command>
.\" termin.al-summary: Show a command manual.
.TH MAN 1 "" "termin.al" "termin.al Manual"
.ftr B R
.ftr I R
.ftr BI R
.SH NAME
man \- Show a command manual.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
man <command>
man -P less|vi <command>
man --pager=less|vi <command>
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
Opens the checked section-1 manual for a registered command. Command aliases resolve through the live registry to one canonical manual. The default and explicit less modes use the same less-style raw pager; vi mode uses the same generated text with a highlighted current line and NORMAL status.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI "-P " "less|vi"
Select the pager. This option must be first, followed by a separate selector and exactly one command name.
.TP
.BI "--pager=" "less|vi"
Select the pager with one option token, followed by exactly one command name.
.PP
The two forms cannot be combined. The superseded selector
.B vim
is unsupported, and
.B --pager vi
or
.B -Pvi
are not accepted spellings.
.SH VIEWER
Both modes show at most 20 source lines per page. j/k or arrows move one line; PageUp/b moves back; PageDown/Space or Ctrl+f moves forward; g/G jumps to start/end; q or Escape closes. In vi mode the current source line is marked and the status reports NORMAL plus line position. In less mode an inverse prompt reports the page position.
.PP
Ctrl+b remains the pane prefix and takes precedence over pager b. Mobile controls expose Esc, up/down and Prefix. Lines wrap to the pane width without horizontal scrolling.
.SH FAILURES
Missing or extra operands, unsupported option forms, an empty selector, unsupported pagers and unregistered command names are rejected. A registered command whose generated artifact is absent reports no manual entry.
.SH NOTES
All routes consume the same build-generated UTF-8 artifact. Closing returns to the owning shell with its transcript, history and current directory unchanged; pager position is not persisted.
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
$ man grep
$ man -P less pane
$ man --pager=vi theme
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
help(1), less(1), pane(1)
